Iunius Brutus.¹ With regard to the date of Juvenal's birth there hasbeen wide divergenee of opinion.² If we accept the statement of the ancient biographies that he practised declamation until middle life,³ then, by a backward calcu- lation from the time when the satires began to be published, we may arrive approximately at the date sought. If the first book was published about the year 105, and Juvenal was then in middle life, he must have been born not long before the year 60. There seems no reason to doubt that his birthplace was Aquinum in Latium, the town near which the inscribed. tablet⁴ set up by Iunius Iuvenalis was found and with which the poet's allusion in the third satire shows intimate acquaintance.⁵
